OL,7,FCity Council leader John Cotton
OL,8,Fapologised to the people of the city
OL,9,Ffor the "unprecedented" cuts, telling
OL,10,Fcouncillors the "budget before council
OL,11,Ftoday is not the budget I entered
OL,12,Fpolitics to set".
OL,14,FThe financial measures have been
OL,15,Fdescribed by councillors on the Labour-
OL,16,Fled council as "devastating".
OL,18,FMr Cotton apologised "unreservedly" to
OL,19,Fpeople living in the city during the
OL,20,Fmeeting on Tuesday.
