OL,7,F"Progress is being made, and I want to
OL,8,Fplace on record my thanks to members,
OL,9,Fto officers and the commissioners who
OL,10,Fare working tirelessly to resolve
OL,11,Fthese critical issues," he said.
OL,13,FBut Mr Cotton said the mistakes made
OL,14,Fin Birmingham had "not occurred in a
OL,15,Fvacuum" and councils up and down the
OL,16,Fland were facing a perfect storm of
OL,17,Fsmaller budgets but higher costs,
OL,18,Fleading to widespread cuts to waste
OL,19,Fcollection, road repairs and leisure
OL,20,Fservices.
